<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="185" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="185">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" author="Braun, U" journalOrPublisher="Schlechtendalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" refId="B2" refString="Braun, U, Nakashima, C, Crous, PW, Groenewald, JZ, Moreno-Rico, O, Rooney-Latham, S, Blomquist, CL, Haas, J, Marmolejo, J, 2018. Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41-99. https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" title="Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41 - 99." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" year="2018">Braun et al. (2018)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Nakash., Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 80" authorityYear="2018" class="Ascomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Tubakia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Tubakia dryinoides" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Tubakia dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on morphological and molecular data. The holotype of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. dryinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">T. dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(NBRC H-11618) was collected from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.Gray" authorityYear="1859" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus phillyraeoides" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="phillyraeoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Quercus phillyraeoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A. Gray (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" author="Braun, U" journalOrPublisher="Schlechtendalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" refId="B2" refString="Braun, U, Nakashima, C, Crous, PW, Groenewald, JZ, Moreno-Rico, O, Rooney-Latham, S, Blomquist, CL, Haas, J, Marmolejo, J, 2018. Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41-99. https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" title="Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41 - 99." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" year="2018">Braun et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In our current research, isolate (SAUCC 1924) collected from diseased leaves of 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Quercus palustris" order="Fagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="palustris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Quercus palustris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clustered in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C. Nakash., Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 80" authorityYear="2018" class="Ascomycetes" family="Clavicipitaceae" genus="Tubakia" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Tubakia dryinoides" order="Diaporthales" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">Tubakia dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
clade by strong support (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogram of Tubakiaceae, based on the concatenated ITS, LSU and rpb 2 sequence alignment. The BI and ML bootstrap support values above 0.74 and 74 % are shown at the first and second position, respectively. The tree is rooted to Greeneria uvicola (culture FI 12007) and ex-type cultures are indicated in bold face. Strains from the current study are in red. Some branches were shortened for layout purposes - these are indicated by two diagonal lines with the number of times a branch was shortened indicated next to the lines." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.84.73940.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/613632" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">1</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Phylogram of Tubakiaceae, based on the concatenated ITS, tef 1 and tub 2 sequence alignment. The BI and ML bootstrap support values above 0.74 and 74 % are shown at the first and second position, respectively. The tree is rooted to Greeneria uvicola (culture FI 12007) and ex-type cultures are indicated in bold face. Strains from the current study are in red. Some branches were shortened for layout purposes - these are indicated by two diagonal lines with the number of times a branch was shortened indicated next to the lines." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.84.73940.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/613633" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">2</figureCitation>
). We, therefore, consider the isolated strain (SAUCC 1924) as 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. dryinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">T. dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The conidiomata of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. dryinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">T. dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from true pycnothyria and the sporodochial conidiomata of the isolated strain (SAUCC 1924) is new for 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. dryinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">T. dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" author="Braun, U" journalOrPublisher="Schlechtendalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" refId="B2" refString="Braun, U, Nakashima, C, Crous, PW, Groenewald, JZ, Moreno-Rico, O, Rooney-Latham, S, Blomquist, CL, Haas, J, Marmolejo, J, 2018. Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41-99. https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" title="Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41 - 99." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" year="2018">Braun et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, the conidia of our isolate (SAUCC 1924) is narrower than the original description of 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. dryinoides" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" rank="species" species="dryinoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="185">T. dryinoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(4.0-6.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
vs. 5.5-10.0 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" author="Braun, U" journalOrPublisher="Schlechtendalia" pageId="0" pageNumber="185" refId="B2" refString="Braun, U, Nakashima, C, Crous, PW, Groenewald, JZ, Moreno-Rico, O, Rooney-Latham, S, Blomquist, CL, Haas, J, Marmolejo, J, 2018. Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41-99. https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" title="Phylogeny and taxonomy of the genus Tubakias. lat. Fungal Systematics and Evolution 1: 41 - 99." url="https://doi.org/10.3114/fuse.2018.01.04" year="2018">Braun et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
